'''短葉絲蘭'''（{{lang-xm|Yucca brevifolia}}），又名'''約書亞樹'''，為[[天門冬科|天門冬科]][[絲蘭屬|絲蘭屬]]下的一個物種<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.oldone.net/TravelGuide/US_NP/JoshuaTree/PalmJoshuaTree.html |title=棕櫚和約書亞樹 |access-date=2015-06-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130817095238/http://www.oldone.net/TravelGuide/US_NP/JoshuaTree/PalmJoshuaTree.html |archive-date=2013-08-17 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>，屬[[單子葉植物|單子葉]][[樹木|樹木]]，分布於[[美國西南部|美國西南部]]乾燥地區，包括[[加州|加州]]、[[亞利桑那州|亞利桑那州]]、[[猶他州|猶他州]]、[[內華達州|內華達州]]至西北[[墨西哥|墨西哥]]（[[下加利福尼亞|下加利福尼亞]]、[[南下加利福尼亞州|南下加利福尼亞州]]、[[錫那羅亞|錫那羅亞]]與[[索諾拉沙漠|索諾拉沙漠]]）<ref name="POWO_270297-2">{{cite web |title=''Yucca brevifolia'' Engelm. |work=Plants of the World Online |publisher=Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew |url=http://www.plantsoftheworldonline.org/taxon/urn:lsid:ipni.org:names:270297-2 |access-date=2020-06-25 |archive-date=2021-11-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211111221151/http://www.plantsoftheworldonline.org/taxon/urn:lsid:ipni.org:names:270297-2 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，主要生長於[[莫哈韋沙漠|莫哈韋沙漠]][[約書亞樹國家公園|約書亞樹國家公園]]海拔介於{{convert|400|and|1,800|m|ft|abbr=on}}之間的空曠草原（{{le|女王山谷|Queen Valley}}與{{le|失馬山谷|Lost Horse Valley}}）。其他主要分布地區包括[[莫哈維縣|莫哈維縣]]的[[金曼_(亞利桑那州)|金曼]]；及連接[[威肯勃格_(亞利桑那州)|威肯勃格]]與[[威基阿普_(亞利桑那州)|威基阿普]][[93號美國國道|93號美國國道]]沿路，也因此該條公路被指定為是亞利桑那州的約書亞樹大道<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.arizonahighways.com/explore/scenic-drives/joshua-tree-parkway|title=Joshua Tree Parkway|work=Arizona Highways|date=3 August 2014|publisher=Arizona Department of Transportation|access-date=2020-12-06|archive-date=2021-09-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210923212151/https://www.arizonahighways.com/explore/scenic-drives/joshua-tree-parkway|dead-url=no}}</ref>。除此之外，曾有一片茂密的短葉絲蘭樹林坐落於{{le|莫哈維自然保護區|Mojave National Preserve}}的{{le|西瑪火山場|Cima volcanic field}}，但該處已於2020年8月的一場大火中焚毀<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.desertsun.com/story/news/2020/08/17/dome-fire-burns-in-mojave-national-park-as-temps-soar/3383180001/|title=Dome Fire torches 43,000 acres in Mojave National Preserve, many Joshua trees burned|access-date=2021-10-02|archive-date=2021-09-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210926113516/https://www.desertsun.com/story/news/2020/08/17/dome-fire-burns-in-mojave-national-park-as-temps-soar/3383180001/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

==分類學==
短葉絲蘭於西班牙語中被稱為「''izote de desierto''」，意思為「沙漠之匕首」<ref name=ITIS>{{cite web|url=https://www.itis.gov/servlet/SingleRpt/SingleRpt?search_topic=TSN&search_value=43116|title=Yucca|work=Itis Report|publisher=Integrated Taxonomic Information System|access-date=2012-03-30|archive-date=2021-10-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211003062025/https://www.itis.gov/servlet/SingleRpt/SingleRpt?search_topic=TSN&search_value=43116|dead-url=no}}</ref>，最早在1871年由{{le|喬治·恩格曼|George Engelmann}}於西經100度線地質探勘（或稱「{{le|惠勒勘測|Wheeler Survey}}」）時<ref name="IPNI">{{cite web|work=International Plant Names Index|url=http://www.ipni.org/ipni/idPlantNameSearch.do?id=543655-1&back_page=%2Fipni%2FeditSimplePlantNameSearch.do%3Ffind_wholeName%3DYucca%2Bbrevifolia%26output_format%3Dnormal|title=''Yucca brevifolia'' Engelm.|access-date=2008-12-20|archive-date=2018-11-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181114060332/http://www.ipni.org/ipni/idPlantNameSearch.do?id=543655-1&back_page=%2Fipni%2FeditSimplePlantNameSearch.do%3Ffind_wholeName%3DYucca%2Bbrevifolia%26output_format%3Dnormal|dead-url=no}}</ref>發現並進行命名發表。

短葉絲蘭的別名約書亞樹最早是由19世紀中期的一群[[摩爾門教徒|摩爾門教徒]]移民於跨越莫哈韋沙漠所命名，這種樹扮演了在沙漠中指引他們的角色，且它們的獨特外型就如同[[約書亞|約書亞]]伸直的手臂，引領著他們前往上帝耶和華的應許之地[[迦南|迦南]]({{bibleverse||Joshua|8:18–26|KJV}})<ref name=jtnp>{{cite web |url= http://www.nps.gov/jotr/naturescience/jtrees.htm |work= Nature and Science: Joshua Trees |title= Joshua Tree National Park |publisher= [[National_Park_Service|National Park Service]] |access-date= 2013-05-27 |archive-date= 2015-02-25 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20150225182521/http://www.nps.gov/jotr/naturescience/jtrees.htm |dead-url= no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://travel.nationalgeographic.com/travel/national-parks/joshua-tree-national-park/ |title= Joshua Tree National Park |publisher= [[National_Geographic_Society|National Geographic Society]] |access-date= 2013-05-27 |archive-date= 2016-12-01 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20161201113837/http://travel.nationalgeographic.com/travel/national-parks/joshua-tree-national-park |dead-url= no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.usanpn.org/cpp/YUBR |title= Joshua Tree (Yucca brevifolia) |work= Meet the Species: All Species |publisher= The California Phenology Project, USA National Phenology Network |access-date= 2013-05-27 |archive-date= 2015-07-06 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20150706234509/https://www.usanpn.org/cpp/YUBR |dead-url= no }}</ref>；此外，蓬亂的的葉子外型也與鬍鬚相似<ref>{{cite book |last=Peattie |first=Donald Culross |author-link=Donald C. Peattie |title=A Natural History of Western Trees |year=1953 |publisher=[[Bonanza_Books|Bonanza Books]] |location=New York |page=304}}</ref>。然而，並無直接或間接的證明能證實這樣的命名起源，唯一的證據就是在摩爾門教徒到來之後，才有了約書亞樹這樣的別稱出現<ref name=jtnp/><ref>{{cite book |last=Zarki |first=Joseph |date=2015 |title=Joshua Tree National Park |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=U2NWBwAAQBAJ |location=Charleston, South Carolina |publisher=Arcadia Publishing |page=28 |isbn=9781467132817 |access-date=2021-10-02 |archive-date=2021-09-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210926113508/https://books.google.com/books?id=U2NWBwAAQBAJ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。另外，短葉絲蘭的外型比起約書亞，更像是《[[出埃及記|出埃及記]]》中身處[[利非訂|利非訂]]時的[[摩西|摩西]]<ref>{{cite magazine |last=Saunders |first=Charles Francis |date=1929 |title=Why Joshua Tree? |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=yRAmAQAAMAAJ |magazine=Desert |access-date=January 11, 2019 |volume=1 |page=80 |quote=An application to Mr. [[Frederick_Vernon_Coville|Frederick V. Coville]], botanist of the Department of Agriculture, elicited the following response: 'The statement is often made that this name Joshua-tree was applied to ''Cleistoyucca brevifolia'' because it was this tree which led the Mormons through the desert. I have no means of knowing, however, whether this explanation is authentic or whether it was invented as an explanation of the name. It seems to me more likely that Joshua tree is a garbled Indian name' […] I asked Professor [[Marcus_E._Jones|Marcus E. Jones]], whose knowledge of the desert flora is unsurpassed, and who has had a long acquaintance with members of the Mormon church. In reply, he kindly wrote as follows: 'The Mormon church officials do not know exactly the origin of the term, but assume that it is from the wide-spreading arms (branches) that in the night remind of the time when in battle Joshua had his arms held up in order to win a battle. This I got from one of the twelve apostles of the Mormon church.' Plausible as this explanation is, its value is more or less shaken when one finds, as I did after looking up the family Bible, that it was Moses, not Joshua, who had his arms held up during the battle, while Joshua conducted the fighting (Ex. 17:8–13). There is, however, another account of a fight, which may be what the Mormon apostle had in mind. It is told in the book of Joshua 7:18–26 [sic]. |archive-date=2021-10-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211011170034/https://books.google.com/books?id=yRAmAQAAMAAJ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

與摩爾門教徒移民同時來到此地的牧場主與礦工會利用短葉絲蘭的枝幹做成圍欄或蒸汽引擎的替代燃料，他們稱倒下的短葉絲蘭為特維斯（''tevis''）樹樁<ref>{{cite web |last1=Jane |first1=Rodgers |title=Vegetation Specialist |url=https://www.nps.gov/jotr/learn/nature/jtrees.htm |website=Joshua Tree |access-date=6 October 2020 |archive-date=2015-02-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150225182521/http://www.nps.gov/jotr/naturescience/jtrees.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

除了{{le|種名|Autonym (botany)}}[[亞種|亞種]]''Y. b.'' subsp. ''brevifolia''外，也包含了其他兩個亞種<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.yuccaagavaceae.com/species.html |title=Yucca species |publisher=Yuccaagavaceae.com |access-date=2012-03-30 |archive-date=2021-04-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210423220124/http://www.yuccaagavaceae.com/species.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>：''Y. b.'' subsp. ''herbertii''（赫伯特短葉絲蘭）及''Y. b.'' subsp. ''jaegeriana''（耶格爾短葉絲蘭），不過它們有時也被視為是[[變種|變種]]<ref name=ITIS/><ref name=Grandtner2005>{{Cite book| last = Grandtner| first = Miroslav M.| year = 2005| title = Elsevier's Dictionary of Trees - North America| page = 973| url = https://books.google.com/books?id=yjc5ZYWtkNAC&q=Yucca+brevifolia&pg=PA973| isbn = 978-0-444-51784-5| publisher = Elsevier| location = Amsterdam| access-date = 2021-10-02| archive-date = 2021-10-10| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20211010013358/https://books.google.com/books?id=yjc5ZYWtkNAC&q=Yucca+brevifolia&pg=PA973| dead-url = no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cnpsci.org/html/PlantInfo/ChecklistofVenturaCountyRarePlants-19Sep2005.pdf|title=Checklist of Ventura County Rare Plants|publisher=California National Plant Society, Channel Islands Chapter|first=David L.|last=Magney|date=2005-09-19|access-date=2012-03-30|archive-date=2021-09-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210926113509/http://www.cnpsci.org/html/PlantInfo/ChecklistofVenturaCountyRarePlants-19Sep2005.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>或{{le|變型|Form (botany)}}<ref name=Egglid2001>{{cite book | last = Eggli | first =  Urs | year = 2001 | title = Monocotyledons  | pages = 90–91, 100 | isbn = 978-3-540-41692-0 | publisher = Springer | location = Berlin }}</ref>。或是如短葉絲蘭的亞種''Y. b.'' subsp. ''jaegeriana''，有時被視為是獨立種<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Lenz|first=Lee|date=2007-07-25|title=Reassessment of Yucca brevifolia and Recognition of Y. jaegeriana as a Distinct Species|url=https://scholarship.claremont.edu/aliso/vol24/iss1/7|journal=Aliso: A Journal of Systematic and Evolutionary Botany|volume=24|issue=1|pages=97–104|doi=10.5642/aliso.20072401.07|issn=0065-6275|doi-access=free|access-date=2021-10-02|archive-date=2021-09-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210926113510/https://scholarship.claremont.edu/aliso/vol24/iss1/7/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

==描述==
短葉絲蘭為快速生長的沙漠物種，新生的幼苗於前十年每年能成長{{convert|7.6|cm|in|1|abbr=on}}，而在這之後每年生長約{{convert|3.8|cm|in|1|abbr=on}}<ref name="Keith 1982">{{cite journal | last1 = Keith | first1 = Sandra L | year = 1982 | title = A tree named Joshua | url = https://archive.org/details/sim_american-forests_1982-07_88_7/page/40 | journal = American Forests | volume = 88 | issue = 7| pages = 40–42 }}</ref>。樹幹由上千的小[[纖維|纖維]]所組成，缺乏[[年輪|年輪]]，這讓它們的樹齡難以被判定。具有深而發達的根系，深度可達{{convert|11|m|ft|0|abbr=on}}<ref name="Gucker 2006">{{cite web|last1=Gucker|first1=Corey L.|year=2006|url=http://www.fs.fed.us/database/feis/plants/tree/yucbre/all.html|title=Yucca brevifolia|work=Fire Effects Information System|publisher=[[U.S._Department_of_Agriculture|U.S. Department of Agriculture]], Forest Service, Rocky Mountain Research Station, Fire Sciences Laboratory|access-date=2008-12-20|archive-date=2018-11-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181114141416/https://www.fs.fed.us/database/feis/plants/tree/yucbre/all.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。如果能撐過沙漠的嚴酷環境，短葉絲蘭的壽命可達數百年，甚至一千年。樹高可達{{convert|15|m|ft|0|abbr=on}}。新植株可透過[[種子|種子]]繁殖，或是透過母株的地下[[根莖|根莖]]重新長出新植株。

[[常綠植物|常綠]][[葉|葉]]呈暗綠色，基部寬度{{cvt|7|to|15|mm}}，為細長的刺刀狀，長度約{{cvt|15|to|35|cm}}。葉片排列呈螺旋狀排列叢生於莖部頂端，葉緣為白色並具有[[鋸齒|鋸齒]]。
[[File:Joshua_Tree_Panicle_1.jpg|thumb]]綻放的花朵]]

[[花|花]]期為每年的二月至四月底，為[[圓錐花序|圓錐花序]]，花序高{{cvt|30|to|55|cm}}、直徑{{cvt|30|to|38|cm}}, 單一花朵長{{cvt|4|to|7|cm}}，具有六枚奶油白至綠色{{le|葉片形態學詞匯表|Glossary of leaf morphology|矛形}}的[[花被片|花被片]]。[[雌蕊|雌蕊]]長{{cvt|3|cm}}，柱頭腔被裂瓣所圍繞。半肉質的果實為棕綠色，呈橢圓形，內有許多扁平的種子。短葉絲蘭多半只有在開花之後才會開始分枝（或是當其生長點被[[象鼻蟲|象鼻蟲]]啃食破壞時）。它們並不會每年開花，而是和其他沙漠植物一樣，必須有合適的降雨情況為前提，並且必須先經歷過寒冬的低溫刺激。

當它們開花時，花朵會吸引{{le|絲蘭蛾科|Prodoxidae|絲蘭蛾}}（''{{le|Tegeticula synthetica}}''）前來授粉，牠們在將卵產在花朵內的同時也會沾上花粉。絲蘭蛾的[[幼體|幼體]]主要以種子為食，但短葉絲蘭仍能保有足夠數量的種子進行繁殖。此外，短葉絲蘭也會提早使上面沾有過多蛾卵的花或果實脫落。

==棲息與分佈地==
[[File:JoshuaTreeFruit_2008-06-19-25.jpg|thumb]]
短葉絲蘭主要分布於[[美國西南部|美國西南部]]乾燥地區，包括[[加州|加州]]、[[亞利桑那州|亞利桑那州]]、[[猶他州|猶他州]]、[[內華達州|內華達州]]至西北[[墨西哥|墨西哥]]（[[下加利福尼亞|下加利福尼亞]]、[[南下加利福尼亞州|南下加利福尼亞州]]、[[錫那羅亞|錫那羅亞]]與[[索諾拉沙漠|索諾拉沙漠]]）<ref name="POWO_270297-2"/>，約與[[莫哈韋沙漠|莫哈韋沙漠]]地理位置範圍相同<ref name="Gucker 2006" />，被視為是該沙漠的[[生物指標|生物指標]]，主要分布海拔介於{{convert|400|and|1,800|m|ft|abbr=on}}之間<ref name="Gossard 1992">{{cite book|last=Gossard|first=G|year=1992|title=The Joshua Tree, a Controversial, Contradictory Desert Centurion|publisher=Yellow Rose Publications}}</ref>。

===保育現況===
短葉絲蘭被認為是會受到[[氣候變遷|氣候變遷]]影響而改變分布範圍的物種之一<ref name="ShafBartThom01">{{Cite journal |last1=Shafer |first1=Sarah L. |last2=Bartlein |first2=Patrick J. |last3=Thompson |first3=Robert S. |year=2001 |title=Potential changes in the distributions of western North America tree and shrub taxa under future climate scenarios |journal=Ecosystems |volume=4 |issue=3 |pages=200–215 |doi=10.1007/s10021-001-0004-5|citeseerx=10.1.1.569.228 |s2cid=6214861 }}</ref>，並在之後可能會完全於約書亞樹國家公園中消失，且於21世紀結束前現有分佈範圍內的短葉絲蘭植株數量將減少90%<ref name="Cole2011">{{cite journal|last1=Cole|first1=Kenneth L.|first2=Kirsten|last2=Ironside|first3=Jon|last3=Eischeid|first4=Gregg|last4=Garfin|first5=Phillip B.|last5=Duffy|first6=Chris|last6=Toney|year=2011|title=Past and ongoing shifts in Joshua tree distribution support future modeled range contraction|journal=Ecological Applications|volume=21|issue=1|pages=137–149|url=http://www.fs.fed.us/rm/pubs_other/rmrs_2011_cole_k001.pdf|doi=10.1890/09-1800.1|pmid=21516893|access-date=2021-10-02|archive-date=2021-08-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210809130645/http://www.fs.fed.us/rm/pubs_other/rmrs_2011_cole_k001.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="NPR">{{cite web |url=https://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=17628032 |title=Outlook Bleak for Joshua Trees |publisher=National Public Radio |date=2008-02-04 |access-date=2012-03-30 |archive-date=2021-09-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210926113508/https://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=17628032 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2019/aug/10/joshua-tree-extinct-mojave-desert-climate-change|title='It makes me angry': is this the end for America's Joshua trees?|last=Singh|first=Maanvi|date=2019-08-10|work=The Guardian|access-date=2019-08-10|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077|archive-date=2021-10-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211027120413/https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2019/aug/10/joshua-tree-extinct-mojave-desert-climate-change|dead-url=no}}</ref>，進而從根本上改變國家公園的生態系。此外，於13,000年前滅絕的{{le|沙斯塔地懶|Nothrotheriops}}糞便化石中曾發現短葉絲蘭的葉片、果實與種子，推測短葉絲蘭和[[酪梨|酪梨]]一樣，均是主要仰賴地懶來散播種子；在地懶滅絕後，短葉絲蘭被認為不再具有遷移至合適氣候的能力<ref name="Cole2011" /><ref name="NPR" />。

==人為種植與運用==
原分布於較東部較小型的短葉絲蘭變型被挑選作為園藝品種，它們的高度僅能達{{cvt|2.5|m}}，約於高{{cvt|1|m}}時分枝<ref name=Harlow2003>{{cite book | editor-last1 = Harlow | editor-first1 = Nora| editor-first2 = Kristin |editor-last2=Jakob | year = 2003| title = Wild lilies, irises, and grasses: gardening with California monocots | page = 215| isbn = 978-0-520-23849-7| publisher = [[University_of_California_Press|University of California Press]]| location = Berkeley}}</ref>。

[[北撲翅鴷|北撲翅鴷]]會在短葉絲蘭的枝幹中築巢，巢穴廢棄後也會被其他鳥類所使用<ref name=Audubon/>。

生活於美國一南部的原住民{{le|卡惠拉族|Cahuilla}}將短葉絲蘭視為是珍貴的資源，並稱其為「''hunuvat chiy'a''」或「''humwichawa''」。他們的祖先會使用短葉絲蘭的葉片來編織涼鞋與籃簍，並食用其種子與花芽，紅色的根則是用作染料<ref name=Audubon>{{cite book |last=Little |first=Elbert L. |title=The Audubon Society Field Guide to North American Trees: Western Region |year=1994 |orig-year=1980 |publisher=Knopf |isbn=0394507614 |edition=Chanticleer Press|page=329}}</ref>。短葉絲蘭的根含有[[醣苷|皂素醣苷]]<ref name=Burdock2005>{{Cite book| last = Burdock | first =  George A. | year = 2005 | title = Fenaroli's handbook of flavor ingredients | url = https://archive.org/details/fenarolishandboo00burd | page = [https://archive.org/details/fenarolishandboo00burd/page/n1941 1913] | isbn = 978-0-8493-3034-6 | publisher = CRC Press | location = Boca Raton, Fla.}}</ref>。

